{"overview":"A brooding ballad in d minor with strong ABA' ternary architecture, this piece's most distinctive feature is its bold enharmonic excursion through D major, B minor, and F# major in the middle section before snapping back to d minor via an enharmonic pivot — a harmonic journey of striking chromatic daring framed by a solemn, hymn-like opening theme evoking the Scottish ballad tradition.","cross_piece_tags":["ballade","ternary","modal_mixture","enharmonic_modulation","chromatic_mediant","arpeggiated_bass","melancholic","dramatic"]}
